        {
            "date": "2010-01-06 15:43:49", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I'd be willing to take a look at this.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Did you have a specific solution in mind?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Looking through the code, it looks like the error really needs to be handled several \nlevels up.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Further, it's not clear to me that the lack of file handles will resolve \nitself without some user action -- should the user be informed of the problem somehow?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Or is there some way to transparently recycle SharedIOBuffers or one of the resource \nhandlers in the chain?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "/u/@UhVUQlFYBxFAVwU%3D/", 
            "email": "/u/@UhVUQlFYBxFAVwU%3D/"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2010-01-06 15:53:05", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I was looking at this from a \"we are temporarily swamped with IPC involving shared memory\" standpoint, \nwhere it will resolve itself if you wait.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "The specific case that triggered my filing this bug was a page cycler test \nthat opened a page with a *ton* of images which, since they were local and therefore not throttled by max \nconnections per server, all tried to load at once.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "If the process is persistently out of fd's, there's probably not \ntoo much we can realistically do.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "My hope was that it would be architecturally feasible to make some requests wait when there were too many \nSharedMemory objects currently active, but I hadn't dug in beyond that.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "There was a short thread back when I \nfirst found this:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "https://groups.google.com/group/chromium-", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "dev/browse_thread/thread/e1836dc16a192454/edba3177f8caf4ee", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "/u/stuartmorgan@chromium.org/", 
            "email": "/u/stuartmorgan@chromium.org/"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2010-01-06 16:09:02", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "It looks pretty straightforward to make SharedMemory::CreateOrOpen block for some time \nif a fd isn't available.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Would a poll/sleep block at that level do enough to let \nother threads release their own shared memory fds?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I'll work up a patch to give us \nsomething concrete to discuss.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "/u/@UhVUQlFYBxFAVwU%3D/", 
            "email": "/u/@UhVUQlFYBxFAVwU%3D/"
